2 SENATE BILL 1044
1 (4) “TYPE I SCHOOL VEHICLE” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
2 11–173 OF THE TRANSPORTATION ARTICLE.
3 (5) “TYPE II SCHOOL VEHICLE” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
4 11–174 OF THE TRANSPORTATION ARTICLE.
5 (B) THE STATE BOARD SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO ALLOW THE USE OF
6 ALTERNATIVE SCHOOL VEHICLES TO TRANSPORT STUDENTS TO AND FROM SCHOOL:
7 (1) (I) IF A COUNTY BOARD DETERMINES THAT IT IS NECESSARY TO
8 OWN, OPERATE, OR CONTRACT THE USE OF AN ALTERNATIVE SCHOOL VEHICLE TO
9 TRANSPORT STUDENTS TO AND FROM SCHOOL; OR
10 (II) IF THE VEHICLE IS:
11 1. A TAXICAB;
12 2. A COMMERCIAL MOTOR COACH; OR
13 3. OPERATED BY A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
14 OPERATOR PROVIDING TRANSPORTATION NETWORK SERVICES, AS DEFINED IN §
15 10–101 OF THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE; AND
16 (2) REGARDLESS OF WHETHER THE VEHICLE:
17 (I) TRANSPORTS MORE THAN ONE STUDENT;
18 (II) HAS AN AUDIBLE BACK–UP WARNING ALARM INSTALLED
19 BEHIND THE REAR AXLE;
20 (III) HAS A FIRST AID KIT;
21 (IV) HAS A FLUID CLEANUP KIT;
22 (V) HAS A FIRE EXTINGUISHER; OR
23 (VI) HAS A SEAT BELT CUTTER THAT IS ACCESSIBLE TO THE
24 DRIVER.
25 (C) (1) THE REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL
26 REQUIRE ALTERNATIVE SCHOOL VEHICLES ALLOWED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
27 THIS SECTION AND MULTIFUNCTION SCHOOL ACTIVITY BUSES TO:

SENATE BILL 1044 3
1 (I) UNDERGO TWO INSPECTIONS EACH SCHOOL YEAR THAT
2 ARE MORE THAN 120 DAYS APART; AND
3 (II) BE INSPECTED BY TECHNICIANS CERTIFIED BY THE
4 NATIONAL INSTITUTE FOR AUTOMOTIVE SERVICE EXCELLENCE.
5 (2) RECORDS OF EACH INSPECTION REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH
6 (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE MAINTAINED BY:
7 (I) THE CONTRACTED TRANSPORTATION PROVIDER; OR
8 (II) IF A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM OWNS THE ALTERNATIVE
9 SCHOOL VEHICLE OR MULTIFUNCTION SCHOOL ACTIVITY BUS, THE
10 TRANSPORTATION OFFICE OF THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2025.

